insert into hudsonu.event values(345510,'Heritage Dinner',cast('2014-02-28 18:00' as date),cast('2014-02-28 20:00' as date),'The Edge Cafe',NULL,NULL,'BSU','The Black Student Union annually hosts the Heritage Dinner on the last day of Black History Month. We host this event because it is open to all students, faculty and staff on Hudson University as well as the community members of Hamilton. The Heritage Dinner is a way for BSU to end Black History Month on a good note by providing good food, good company and good discussion.',700);
insert into hudsonu.event values(345512,'Black History Month Release Night',cast('2014-02-21 18:00' as date),cast('2014-02-21 20:00' as date),'ALANA Lounge',NULL,NULL,'BSU','Release Night is an opportunity for students on campus to express themselves and speak on social, political, and economic concerns that they have been pondering. It is a welcoming and encouraging space for dialogue to occur on the basis of the type of concerns, questions, and aspirations that Hudson students raise to one another. The Black Student Union takes great pride in celebrating students voices. Through the hosting of Release Nights we provide this platform.'||chr(10)||'Essentially, it is a chance to gain support and recognition through others about the struggles and achievements that Hudson students may be enduring. Students are provided a support structure, which allows them to openly voice their thoughts without fear of being judged.',410);
