insert into hudsonu.event values(474887,'Ebola in Africa: Deadly Threat or Media Hype?',cast('2014-09-18 11:15' as date),cast('2014-09-18 11:15' as date),'Lawrence 105 (Ho Lecture Room)',NULL,NULL,'HGHC','Ebola has been prominently in the news recently, with over 2000 cases this year in western Africa. This outbreak has raised many questions, including: where does Ebola come from; how does it cause disease; and how it is transmitted? Why has the current outbreak has gained such a high level of attention? Is Ebola a threat to a wider region of Africa or even the US? Associate Professor Geoff Holm will answer these questions and more about the biology and epidemiology of Ebola at a Brown Bag Lunch, sponsored by the Hudson Global Health Initiative. Thursday, September 18, at 11:20 in the Ho Lecture Room in Lawrence Hall.',350);
