insert into hudsonu.event values(708410,'LASO Keynote Speaker: Mayda Del Valle',cast('2015-09-23 16:00' as date),cast('2015-09-23 17:00' as date),'Love Auditorium','Arts',NULL,'LASO','The Latin American Student Organization (LASO), in conjunction with Lounge, has invited Mayda Del Valle to act as the Keynote speaker for the 2015 fall semester Hispanic Heritage Month celebration. Mayda will recite original poetry pertinent to Hispanic Heritage Month and to latino culture.  Mayda Del Valle will perform at Hudson University on September 23rd in Love Auditorium in the afternoon and will be followed by a Q and A session and dinner with LASO members and related faculty on the same day.'||chr(10)||'Mayda is a puerto rican poet who is renowned for her autobiographical narratives in the form of spoken word poetry and music. She grew up in South Chicago where the hybrid identity and experience that resonates throughout her work emerged. She combines the urban hispanic experience and female experience with the English and Spanish language mixed with hip-hop, classic and contemporary latino music influences. As she refined her Slam Poetry style , she integrated these themes into her works and was able to develop many comprehensive pieces that questioned and examined societys current attitudes towards these topics. Mayda has been featured in Latina Magazine, The Source, The New York Times and was named by Smithsonian Magazine as one of Americas Young Innovators in the Arts and Sciences. Oprahs O Magazine selected her as one of 20 women for their first ever O Power List, a group of visionary women making a mark in business, politics, and the arts. In May of 2009 she was invited to perform at the White House for President Obama and the First Lady. She seeks to challenge traditional western approaches to perform by creating a communal participatory space where the audiences are invited to journey through their own cultural narratives and mythologies. We hope to make Hudson one of those spaces where her art and story can be expressed.',500);
